title: Fix segment number

title: `Accept` connection improvements
body:
* Part of #13 and #6.
* Changes `accept_buffer_map` to `accept_buffer_queue`; the order is important here so we address `Accept` requests in an FIFO manner
* Small change to `buffer_client_hello`; if we find that there are unhandled client-hellos in the queue, then we take care of those first and buffer in the incoming-packet as unhandled
* Changes above allows us to sustain multiple-clients spawning multiple connection requests.

title: Working handshake + cleanup
body:
* Updated docs to reflect current state
* Lots of code cleanup
* Fixed bug where we re-registered the `temp_key` for the pack leader after the client-hello was found instead of registering the 'real' connection key
* Verified working handshake between client <-> pack-leader
* Re-worked the handshake handling
* Addresses #6

title: Working buffered read and worker jobs
body: Addresses most of the read concerns for #6. I need to clean up parts of the code, re-implement a happy path handshake, add documentation for release and examine areas that need improvement. It's kinda slow but at least it works.
